North Carolina Lemon Pie
  --Cook's Country

Crust:
6 oz saltines (53 saltines, ~1 1/2 sleeves)
1/8 tsp salt
10 tbsp unsalted butter, melted
1/4 c light corn syrup

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 350F. Combine saltines and salt in food processor and pulse to coarse crumbs, ~15 pulses. Add melted butter and corn syrup and pulse until crumbs are broken down into oatmeal size pieces, ~15 pulses. Transfer mixture to greased 9" pie tin. Using bottom of dry measuring cup, press crumbs into even layre on bottom and sides of plate, using your hands to keep crumbs from spilling over plate edge. Place plate on baking sheet and bake until light golden brown and fragrant, 17-19 min.

Filling:
14 oz sweetened condensed milk
4 large egg yolks
1/4 c heavy cream
1 tbsp lemon zest + 1/2 c juice (3 lemons)
1/8 tsp salt

Whisk milk, yolks, cream, zest, and salt in bowl until fully combined. Whisk in lemon juice until fully incorporated. Pour filling into crust (crust doesn't have to be cool). Bake until edges are beginning to set but center still jiggles when shaken, 15-17 min. Place pie on wire rack and let cool completely. Refrigerate pie until fully chilled, ~4 hrs.

Topping:
1/2 c heavy cream, chilled
2 tsp sugar
1/2 tsp vanilla

Using stand mixer fitted with whisk, whip cream, sugar, and vanilla on medium low speed until foamy, ~1 min. Increase speed to high and whip until stiff peaks form, 1-3 min. Spread whipped cream over top of pie. Serve.
